Disaster risk management is a developmental issue aimed at reducing social, economic and environmental disaster losses in order to achieve socio-economic growth in the country. Due to the crosscutting nature of the disaster risk management function, the NDRM Policy is linked to the following social, infrastructure, environmental and natural resources policies:
* National Social Support Policy;
* Malawi Decentralization Policy
* Health Policy;
* National HIV and AIDS Policy;
* Nutrition Policy;
* Food Security Policy;
* Gender Policy;
* Child Protection Policy;
* Education Policy;
* Elderly and Disabilities Policy;
* National Sanitation Policy;

